<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-820] GroovyMain command line switch -i fails when no backup extension is specified</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-820</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The command &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;groovy -pi -e &quot;(line =~ &apos;a&apos;).replaceAll(&apos;b&apos;)&quot; ok.txt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;fails with &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caught: java.io.IOException: unable to rename ok.txt to C:\DOCUME~1\TOMWHI~1\LOC&lt;br/&gt;
ALS~1\Temp\groovy_61377.tmp&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;whereas &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;groovy -pi.bak -e &quot;(line =~ &apos;a&apos;).replaceAll(&apos;b&apos;)&quot; ok.txt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;works fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that after creating a temporary backup file using File.createTempFile() the code needs to delete it before renaming the original to the backup.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached patch file fixes the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
